#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:7
msgid ""
"There are 6 types of user roles with different permission levels in "
"Mattermost: `system admin <#system-admin>`__, `team admin <#team-"
"admin>`__, `channel admin <#channel-admin>`__, `member <#member>`__, "
"`guest <#guest>`__, and `deactivated <#deactivated>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:11
msgid ""
"To view a list of users on the team and what their roles are, you need to"
" be A team admin using Mattermost in a web browser or the desktop app. "
"Open the Team menu and select **Manage Members**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:14
msgid "System admin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:16
msgid ""
"The first user added to a newly-installed Mattermost system is assigned "
"the system admin role. System admins are allowed to perform any actions "
"on the system, and only a system admin can make changes to another system"
" admin user account in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:18
msgid ""
"The system admin is typically a member of the IT staff and has all the "
"privileges of a team admin, along with the following additional "
"privileges:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:20
msgid "Access to the System Console in any team site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:21
msgid ""
"Ability to change any setting on the Mattermost server available in the "
"System Console."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:22
msgid ""
"Ability to promote and demote other users from Member role to system "
"admin role (and vice versa)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:23
msgid "Ability to promote and demote other users to and from Guest role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:24
msgid "Ability to deactivate user accounts and to reactivate them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:25
msgid ""
"Access to private channels, but only if given the link to the private "
"channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:27
msgid ""
"A system admin can view and manage users in **System Console > User "
"Management > Users**. They can search users by name, filter users by "
"teams, and filter to view other system admins, guests, as well as "
"activated and deactivated users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:30
msgid "Grant personal access tokens"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:32
msgid ""
"System admin also can enable `personal access tokens "
"<https://developers.mattermost.com/integrate/admin-guide/admin-personal-"
"access-token/>`__ for user accounts. This gives specific users "
"permissions to create personal access tokens via **System Console > "
"Users**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:34
msgid ""
"In addition, a system admin can optionally set the following permissions "
"for the account, which are useful for integrations and bot accounts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:36
msgid ""
"**post:all**: Allows the account to post to all Mattermost channels "
"including direct messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:37
msgid ""
"**post:channels**: Allows the account to post to all Mattermost public "
"channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:40
msgid "Team admin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:42
msgid ""
"When a team is first created, the person who set it up is made a team "
"admin. It is a team-specific role, meaning that someone can be a team "
"admin for one team but only a member on another team. Team admins have "
"the following privileges:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:44
msgid "Access to the **Team Settings** menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:45
msgid "Ability to change the team name and import data from Slack export files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:46
msgid ""
"Access to the **Manage Members** menu, where they can control whether "
"team members are a **Member** or a **Team Admin**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:47
msgid ""
"Ability to manage all aspects of a team, such as joining and managing "
"private channels they're not a member of."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:50
msgid "Channel admin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:52
msgid ""
"The person who creates a channel is assigned the channel admin role for "
"that channel. People with the channel admin role have the following "
"privileges:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:54
msgid "Ability to assign the channel admin role to other members of the channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:55
msgid ""
"Ability to remove the channel admin role from other holders of the "
"channel admin role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:56
msgid "Ability to remove members from the channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:57
msgid ""
"Ability to configure channel actions that automate tasks based on trigger"
" conditions, such as :ref:`joining a channel <collaborate/join-leave-"
"channels:join a channel>` or :doc:`sending a message </collaborate/send-"
"messages>` in a channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:59
msgid ""
"Depending on your system configuration, channel admins can be granted "
"special permissions by the system admin to rename and delete channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:62
msgid "Member"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:64
msgid ""
"This is the default role given to users when they join a team. Members "
"have basic permissions on a Mattermost team. See the :doc:`advanced "
"permissions backend infrastructure </onboard/advanced-permissions-"
"backend-infrastructure>` documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:67
msgid "Guest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:69
msgid ""
"A guest is a role with restricted permissions. Guests enable "
"organizations to collaborate with users outside of their organization, "
"and control what channels they are in and who they can collaborate with. "
"See the :doc:`guest accounts </onboard/guest-accounts>` documentation for"
" details on working with guest accounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:72
msgid "Deactivated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:74
msgid ""
"A system admin can deactivate user accounts via **System Console > "
"Users**. A list of all users on the server can be searched and filtered "
"to make finding users easier. Select the user's role and in the menu that"
" opens, then select **Deactivate**. See the :ref:`deactivate user "
"accounts admin <configure/user-management-configuration-"
"settings:deactivate users>` documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:76
msgid ""
"When **Deactivate** is selected, the user is logged out of the system, "
"and receives an error message if they try to log back in. The user no "
"longer appears in channel member lists, and they are removed from the "
"team members list. A deactivated account can also be reactivated from the"
" System Console, in which case the user rejoins channels and teams that "
"they previously belonged to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:78
msgid ""
"Direct message channels with deactivated users are hidden in users' "
"sidebars, but can be reopened using the **More...** button or by pressing"
"  :kbd:`Ctrl` :kbd:`K` on Windows or Linux, or :kbd:`âŒ˜` :kbd:`K` on Mac."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:80
msgid ""
"Mattermost is designed as a system-of-record, so there isn't an option to"
" delete users from the Mattermost system, as such an operation could "
"compromise the integrity of message archives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/collaborate/learn-about-roles.rst:84
msgid ""
"AD/LDAP user accounts can't be deactivated from Mattermost; they must be "
"deactivated from your Active Directory."
msgstr ""

